  <object id="56" name="scroll" x="331" y="238">
   <properties>
    <property name="text">&quot;IMPERIAL DECREE NO. 47 – AUTHORIZATION OF CHEMICAL SUPPRESSION

Issued by Order of the Supreme Command

Section I: Purpose
The use of chemical agents is hereby authorized to suppress insurgent groups, 
eliminate hostile gatherings, and instill order in resistant regions.

Section II: Authorized Agents
The Scientific Division is permitted to develop toxic gas compounds for crowd dispersal, slow-acting agents for area denial, and experimental serums for interrogation.

Section III: Deployment Protocol
Use requires approval from a General or higher authority. Civilian presence is non-restrictive if rebellion is suspected. Affected zones must be sealed for 48 hours.

Section IV: Secrecy Clause
This decree is classified at the highest level. Disclosure will result in immediate execution.

Section V: Enforcement
Failure to comply will be treated as treason against the state.

Signed,
General Raizen</property>
   </properties>
  </object>
  <object id="59" name="letter" x="435" y="260">
   <properties>
    <property name="text">&quot;CONFIDENTIAL DIRECTIVE – OPERATION SILENT DAGGER

To: General Kuroda
From: Supreme Command

The continued existence of the rebel leader in Kyushu poses an unacceptable threat to imperial 
stability.

Objective
Eliminate the rebel leader known as 'Hikari'. Ensure no public trace links this action to the Empire.

Instructions
Deploy covert operatives disguised as night patrol units. Strike during the upcoming festival 
when defenses are lowered. Leave no survivors in the immediate vicinity.

Additional Orders
Retrieve all documents or symbols associated with the rebellion. If capture is possible, 
transport the target to the capital for interrogation.

Final Note
Failure is not an option. The throne grows impatient.

Signed,
Raizen&quot;</property>
   </properties>
  </object>
